@startuml FE234_AreaStatusEvaluate_Sequence
title FE234 - Evaluate Area Flood Status (FeatG34)

actor User
participant UI
participant AreaStatusEvaluateEndpoint
participant MediatR
participant AreaStatusEvaluateHandler
participant Repository
participant Service
database Database

User -> UI: 1. Select area to view status
UI -> AreaStatusEvaluateEndpoint: 2. GET /api/v1/areas/{id}/status
AreaStatusEvaluateEndpoint -> MediatR: 3. Send(AreaStatusEvaluateRequest)
MediatR -> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 4. Handle(request)

AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> Service: 5. GetStatusFromCache(areaId)
alt [Cache Hit]
    Service --> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 6. Return cached response
    AreaStatusEvaluateHandler --> MediatR: 7. Response (from cache)
else [Cache Miss]
    AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> Repository: 8. GetAreaById(id)
    Repository -> Database: 9. SELECT * FROM areas WHERE id = {id}
    Database --> Repository: 10. Area entity
    Repository --> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 11. Area entity

    alt [Area NOT found]
        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler --> MediatR: 12. Response {success: false, message: "Not Found"}
    else [Area exists]
        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> Repository: 13. GetActiveStations()
        Repository -> Database: 14. SELECT * FROM stations...
        Database --> Repository: 15. List<Station>
        Repository --> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 16. List<Station>

        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> Repository: 17. GetLatestReadings(stationIds)
        Repository -> Database: 18. SELECT * FROM readings...
        Database --> Repository: 19. List<Reading>
        Repository --> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 20. List<Reading>

        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> AreaStatusEvaluateHandler: 21. Calculate Weights & Status
        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler -> Service: 22. SaveToCache(areaId, response, 30s)
        AreaStatusEvaluateHandler --> MediatR: 23. Response {success: true, data}
    end
end

MediatR --> AreaStatusEvaluateEndpoint: 24. Response
AreaStatusEvaluateEndpoint --> UI: 25. HTTP 200/404 (AreaStatusDto)
UI --> User: 26. Display Area Flood Status

@enduml
